<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_PIPELINE_STATE_FLAGS">
    <summary>
      <para>Flags to control pipeline state.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This enum is used by the <b>Flags</b> member of the
<see cref="D3D12_GRAPHICS_PIPELINE_STATE_DESC" /> and
<see cref="D3D12_COMPUTE_PIPELINE_STATE_DESC" /> structures.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/direct3d-12-enumerations">Core Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_PIPELINE_STATE_FLAGS.D3D12_PIPELINE_STATE_FLAG_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates no flags.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_PIPELINE_STATE_FLAGS.D3D12_PIPELINE_STATE_FLAG_TOOL_DEBUG">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates that the pipeline state should be compiled with additional information to assist debugging.
This can only be set on WARP devices.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>